cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.RO

This paper deals with visual representation learning, specifically in the context of 3D view prediction and object detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also proposes a novel model architecture and loss function for self-supervised learning, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the role of predictive coding theories in the development of 3D visual recognition, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with disentangling scene content from camera motion, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.RO (Robotics).
